This paper deals with product search, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes an end-to-end context-aware embedding model, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and deep learning (DL) techniques, making cs.CL and cs.CV likely categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses personalization and user preferences, which are related to recommender systems and user modeling, making cs.AI a possible category.
